### Base URL variable
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ============================================================
### USERS — Basic pagination
### ============================================================

### Get all users (default page 1, size 10, order by id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

###

### Page 1, 5 per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=5

###

### Page 2, 5 per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=2&page_size=5

###

### Page 3, 5 per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=3&page_size=5

### ============================================================
### USERS — Sorting (order_by + order_dir)
### ============================================================

### Order by name ASC
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=10&order_by=name&order_dir=asc

###

### Order by name DESC
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=10&order_by=name&order_dir=desc

###

### Order by birth_date ASC
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=10&order_by=birth_date&order_dir=asc

###

### Order by birth_date DESC
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=10&order_by=birth_date&order_dir=desc

###

### Order by email ASC
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&page_size=10&order_by=email&order_dir=asc

###

### Invalid order_by column (should fall back to default: id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?order_by=password&order_dir=asc

### ============================================================
### USERS — Filter by ID
### ============================================================

### Filter by ID = 1 (Alice)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?id=1

###

### Filter by ID = 6 (Frank)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?id=6

###

### Filter by non-existent ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?id=9999

### ============================================================
### USERS — Filter by Name
### ============================================================

### Filter by name containing "alice"
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?name=alice

###

### Filter by name containing "a" (multiple results)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?name=a

###

### Filter by name containing "on"
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?name=on

### ============================================================
### USERS — Filter by Email
### ============================================================

### Filter by email containing "bob"
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?email=bob

###

### Filter by email containing "example"
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?email=example

### ============================================================
### USERS — Filter by Gender
### ============================================================

### Filter female users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?gender=female

###

### Filter male users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?gender=male

###

### Filter other
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?gender=other

### ============================================================
### USERS — Filter by Birth Date
### ============================================================

### Filter by exact birth date
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?birth_date=1995-03-12

###

### Invalid date format (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?birth_date=12-03-1995

### ============================================================
### USERS — Combined filters (3 fields + pagination + order_by)
### ============================================================

### Female users with "a" in name, page 1, size 5, order by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?name=a&gender=female&page=1&page_size=5&order_by=name&order_dir=asc

###

### Male users, ordered by birth_date DESC, page 1, size 5
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?gender=male&page=1&page_size=5&order_by=birth_date&order_dir=desc

###

### Name contains "a", email contains "example", ordered by id, page 1 size 3
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?name=a&email=example&page=1&page_size=3&order_by=id&order_dir=asc

### ============================================================
### COMMON FRIENDS
### ============================================================

### Common friends of Alice (1) and Bob (2) — expects Carol, David, Eva
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=1&user2=2

###

### Common friends of Frank (6) and Grace (7) — expects Henry, Iris, Jack
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=6&user2=7

###

### Users with no common friends
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=19&user2=21

###

### Same user for both (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=1&user2=1

###

### Missing user2 param (expect 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=1

###

### Non-existent users (expect empty result)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/common-friends?user1=999&user2=998
